{"turn": 6, "stop_reason": "end_turn", "usage": {"in": 2, "out": 2300, "cache_read": 11670, "cache_write": 2152}, "blocks": [{"signature": "", "thinking": "", "type": "thinking"}, {"text": "# Executive Summary: Spring Glow Creative Campaign\n\n*(Prepared from internal campaign records; each figure/claim is sourced below. Note: the underlying document set contains overlapping and, in some cases, conflicting cost figures \u2014 these are flagged rather than reconciled by assumption.)*\n\n## Campaign Overview\nSpring Glow was launched by Lumina Beauty Corp to drive a **25% uplift in unit sales of GlowSerum** within six weeks of launch, built around the core message **\"Reawakening Your Natural Radiance.\"** Tactics centered on short-form digital video and micro-influencer content, paired with high-impact in-store retail activation.\n*Source: `brief.txt` \u2014 Campaign Brief memo from Sarah Chen, VP of Marketing Strategy, Oct 26, 2023.*\n\n## Approved Creative Concepts\n- **Final sign-off** was granted for the campaign's core visual assets \u2014 **high-resolution hero imagery and packaging renders** \u2014 submitted for leadership approval as \"Spring Campaign Visual Assets.\"\n *Source: `creative_approved.eml` \u2014 Final Sign-off Request memo, Oct 26, 2023.*\n- Separately, **internal approval was recorded for TVC (television commercial) visuals**, with print assets still pending final sign-off at the time of reporting.\n *Source: `status_report_0674_480.md` \u2014 Weekly Status Report, Sarah Chen, Head of Campaign Management, Dec 2025.*\n\n## Delivery Team / Agency\n- The visual asset sign-off package was delivered by the **\"Project Zenith\" creative team**.\n *Source: `creative_approved.eml`.*\n- Production work was executed by **Melbournescope Studios**, confirmed as the campaign's production vendor.\n *Source: `budget_1720_421.txt` / `budget_1720_421_v1.md`, prepared by Sarah Chen, Jan 28, 2026; corroborated in `memo_0778_234.md`.*\n- Additional vendor partners aligned to campaign goals included **Skyline Analytics** and **Dingo Consulting**.\n *Source: `email_0838_244.txt`.*\n\n## Total Spend\nPer the dedicated creative cost breakdown for the project, itemized Spring Glow creative-related costs total **$54,200**:\n| Category | Amount |\n|---|---|\n| Media | $25,000 |\n| Production | $15,000 |\n| Agency | $8,000 |\n| Talent | $5,000 |\n| Printing | $1,200 |\n| **Total** | **$54,200** |\n*Source: `spring_glow_budget.csv`.*\n\n**\u26a0\ufe0f Discrepancy flag:** Two separate financial memos describing the broader \"Spring Glow Campaign Execution (SGX)\" cite materially different total budgets \u2014 **AUD 435,000** (`budget_1720_421.txt` / `budget_1720_421_v1.md`, Jan 28, 2026) versus **AUD 385,000** (`memo_0778_234.md`, Feb 7, 2026). These figures could not be reconciled against the $54,200 creative-cost breakdown above, and it is unclear from available documents whether SGX is the same initiative as the original Spring Glow brief or an expanded/successor execution phase. **Recommend confirming with Finance/Sarah Chen before citing a single \"total spend\" figure externally.**", "type": "text"}]}
